    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A rare light blue corrosion product found as a contributing factor to the greenish chromatic degradation of azurite in mural paintings, and in the patina of outdoor bronze monuments such as the horses of San Marco in Venice.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
